-- CTC Media’s 18-Plus Audience Share Increases, TNS-Global Says
-- B y   L e o n   L a z a r o f f
-- 2012-06-01T23:01:35Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-01/ctc-media-s-18-plus-audience-share-increases-tns-global-says.html
CTC Media Inc. (CTCM) ’s CTC television
channel increased its share among viewers of 18 years and older
in the week to May 27, according to TNS-Global.  Viewer share for CTC TV, the Nasdaq-listed Russian media
company’s biggest source of revenue, rose to 5.5 percent in the
week to May 27 from 5.4 percent in the previous week, data
researcher TNS-Global said by e-mail today. CTC’s average daily
audience among viewers 4 years old and over gained to 6.3
percent in the week to May 27, from 6.2 percent in the week to
May 20, the data show.  CTC slipped to sixth most-watched television channel among
viewers of 18 years, dropping on notch below REN TV, its nearest
competitor. The average daily share of viewers 18 years or older
for REN TV increased to 5.6 percent in the week to May 27 from
5.2 percent in the week to May 20, the data show. CTC remained
in fifth place among viewers 4 years old and over, TNS-Global
said.  Russia’s government-controlled Rossiya 1 was the most
watched among both audience categories, outpacing  NTV
Television .  Pervyi Kanal  had the third-biggest audience in both
categories, the data show. TNT was the fourth-most watched
channel among viewers, the data showed.  To contact the reporters on this story:
